<body>

  <h1>Crimson Petals</h1>
  <h2>Chapter 2: Rebel's Flame</h2>

  <div class="quote">
    “Kabhi kabhi sach zinda rehne ke liye jhoot ban jaata hai... aur kabhi sach bolna maut se milne jaisa hota hai...”
  </div>

  <div class="line">
    Aria Kiara ke pehlu mein baithi thi. Uska chhota sa haath uski mutthi mein tha — thanda, kamzor, lekin zinda. Par Aria ke paas kuch bhi nahi bacha tha. Na khana, na dawa, na rasta…
  </div>

  <div class="line">
    Tabhi, ek awaaz jungle ke andheron mein goonji: <strong>“Tumhe wahan nahi hona chahiye...”</strong>  
    Ek ladka — <strong>Revan</strong> — jiske haath pe <em>"R13 — Rebellion"</em> ka laal tattoo tha.
  </div>

  <div class="line">
    Revan ne Aria aur Kiara ko District 13 ke tunnel base me le jaane ka offer diya. Wahan aur log the — doctor, hacker, soldier — ek hi mission ke liye:  
    <strong>“System ko jala do, ya usme ghus ke tod do.”</strong>
  </div>

  <div class="line">
    Aria sirf Kiara ko bachana chahti thi, par jab usne dekha ki wahan doctor ne Kiara ka ilaaj kiya — uski aankhon se aansoon ruk nahi paaye.
  </div>

  <div class="line">
    Agle kuch dinon mein Aria ne weapons chalana, fire shots aur maps padhna seekha. Uska vishwas sirf ek baat mein tha:  
    <strong>“Main sirf apne bhai ke liye nahi, sabke bhai-behen ke liye lad rahi hoon.”</strong>
  </div>

  <div class="line">
    Ek raat, Revan ne usse ek chip di — <strong>“Yeh system ka mainframe access key hai.”</strong>  
    Aria ne chip pakdi aur kaha:  
    <div class="quote">“Kranti shuru ho gayi hai.”</div>
  </div>

  <footer>
    Chapter 2 ends • Agla Adhyay: "System Ke Darwaze"
  </footer>

